2095-8927},
   abstract = {Pingdingshan sandstone is a prominent symbol in the upper part of Late Paleozoic strata of North China Block. It is well known for its extensive distribution, special lithology and significant division of sedimentary lithology for the Late Paleozoic strata, suggesting that Pingdingshan sandstone may record a remarkable geological event, however, its sedimentary age and sedimentary environment have always been the focus of controversy for a long time. In this study, samples are selected from the named place of Pingdingshan sandstone in the southern part of North China Block (i. e. Pingdingshan area, Gongyi area and Yiyang area) for LA-ICPMS U-Pb dating of detrital zircons, assisted by Hf isotopes analysis, with the attempt to determine the maximum sedimentary age and the material source area, expecting to provide basis for confirming the sedimentary age and sedimentary environment. The results show that the detrital zircons from four samples of the Pingdingshan sandstone in Pingdingshan, Gongyi and Yiyang areas in the southern part of North China Block, are mainly from the Palaeozoic magmatic zircons and the Precambrian metamorphic zircons. Among them, the Paleozoic zircons account for 13% with the peak age of similar to 259Ma, similar to 318Ma and similar to 435Ma, while the Precambrian zircons account for 87% with distinct peak ages of 1871Ma and 2459Ma, along with two very inconspicuous peak age of similar to 812Ma and similar to 976Ma which is composed by only three zircons. By using the youngest single detrital zircons ages ( YSG) of four samples, 249 8Ma, 260 7Ma, 252 7Ma and 248 7Ma, respectively, which is close to the Permian/Triassic boundary age 251 O. 4Ma, we limit the maximum sedimentary age of the stratum and presume that the bottom of Pingdingshan sandstone may be a contact boundary between Permian and Triassic, i. e., the geological age of the Pingdingshan sandstone in the southern part of North China Block should belong to Early Triassic. Based on analysis of the sedimentary and tectonic setting of Pingdingshan sandstone, accompanied by the comparison with age spectrum and eHf ( t) of the potential material source areas, the main material sources of Pingdingshan sandstone are from the Late Paleozoic intrusive rocks and the metamorphic basement of North China Block in the Inner Mongolia Uplift at the northern part of North China Block, while a few material sources are from the Caledonian middle -acid granitic intrusive rocks and the main metamorphic strata ( Qinling Group, ErlangPing Group and Kuanping Group) in northern Qinling Orogenic Belt. Based on the analysis of the maximum sedimentary ages and sources of Pingdingshan sandstone, with the facts that the provenances of the lower strata ( Shanxi Formation, Xiashihezi Formation and Shangshihezi Formation) are almost all from the Inner Mongolia Uplift in the northern part of North China Block, and the provenances of the upper strata of Shiqianfeng Formation ( except Pingdingshan sandstone) mainly from the North Qinling orogenic belt, it is inferred that the Pingdingshan sandstone may be a record of the sedimentary and tectonic environment change between Permian and Triassic in the southern part of the North China Block.},
