osited approximately 168 million years ago, as inferred from the age of zircons in tuffaceous micrite (160.6 +/- 0.55Ma) at the bottom of the Upper Jurassic Tianchihe Formation (Oxfordian) and the age of zircons in pyroclastic rocks (179.2 +/- 0.79Ma) in the Lower Jurassic Yongdingzhuang Formation (Toarcian). These lines of evidence indicate that initial Jurassic Yanshan movement began 168million years ago during Middle Jurassic time.},
